personal fork of dmenu with the following tweaks:

  > even when there's matches, the first item will be whatever you typed
    so you can select it. this is for cases like using dmenu for history
    and wanting to type something new that happens to match other stuff
  > enable color fonts (requires libxft-bgra-git)

dmenu - dynamic menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dmenu
-------------
See the man page for details.
